Edited somewhat to make the concept more apparent.

+explanation

-know...


The Foundation hasn't (probably, no canon and all that) been around forever, but SCPs have. Those that the Foundation now contains just because they're weird, people of the past probably would have just accepted. On the other hand, some need containment because they're nasty and dangerous. One of those is in Room 166. The rest of 557 is the ancient equivalent of a Foundation facility. Some of the mysterious devices are part of the containment method, while others may be anomalous (at least in the builders' eyes) items themselves.

Now, the rituals that were supposed to help weaken the entity haven't been performed in centuries, and most of the machines keeping it suppressed are broken, and the Foundation currently has no idea how any of it works.




Edited again because Bland's suggestions made much sense.





