SCP-557 is an underground bunker constructed almost entirely of sandstone and mud bricks
附加记录：    



The foundation of SCP-557, as well as all of its exterior and some interior walls, are comprised of sandstone bricks roughly 23 m3. Interior partitions have been constructed in some of the larget chambers, primarily of mud brick
附加记录：    

More than a bit redundant.



So far over █████ such remains have been found, leading researchers to believe that SCP-557 was intended and used as a military complex. This hypothesis is supported by the presence of what appear to be defensive features, although the actual function of these features is uncertain , as some seem to face inward  instead of outward.
附加记录：    

The Foundation is not that dense. If I can figure this out, so can they. There's a difference between implications arising from things left unsaid and painting the Foundation as idiots in order to avoid making statements of the obvious.

